# Tailwind theme tokens (`--app-*`)

When styling with **project theme CSS variables** (e.g. `--app-text`, `--app-hover`), use Tailwind’s **parentheses shorthand** so utilities resolve cleanly and match the linter.

## Prefer

Use `<utility>-(<custom-property-name>)` **without** `var()`:

- `text-(--app-text)`, `text-(--app-text-2)`, `text-(--app-text-3)`
- `bg-(--app-surface)`, `bg-(--app-surface-2)`, `bg-(--app-hover)`, `bg-(--app-selected)`
- `border-(--app-divider)`, `ring-(--app-border)`, `ring-(--app-selected-stroke)`

Modifiers work the same way, e.g. `hover:bg-(--app-hover)`.

## Avoid

Do **not** write arbitrary values like `[color:var(--app-text)]` when the shorthand exists:

- Prefer `text-(--app-text)` over `text-[color:var(--app-text)]`
- Prefer `bg-(--app-surface)` over `bg-[color:var(--app-surface)]`

Keep **conditional** classes composed with `cn()` (see project rule); don’t wrap purely static class strings in `cn()` just to concatenate tokens.
